00:38:46,254 --> 00:38:48,400
Turner小姐说她父亲在金矿区
Miss Turner said that her father had met McCarthy

737
00:38:48,514 --> 00:38:49,688
结识了McCarthy
on the Goldfield.

738
00:38:49,801 --> 00:38:51,569
凭着这些信息我知道方向之所在了
I see the direction, which all this points.

739
00:38:51,681 --> 00:38:52,854
一个来自巴勒拉特的澳大利亚人
An Australian from Ballarat

740
00:38:52,968 --> 00:38:57,096
一个住在这个地区的人
and one who is at home in the district.

741
00:38:57,213 --> 00:39:01,140
要是我没有搞错的话 他来了
Unless I'm very much mistaken, he's here.

742
00:39:02,397 --> 00:39:04,405
John Turner先生来了
Mr. John Turner.

743
00:39:13,183 --> 00:39:15,579
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes.

744
00:39:15,689 --> 00:39:17,977
华生医生
Dr. Watson.

745
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:20,201
我女儿说你们住在这里
My daughter told me you were lodging here.

746
00:39:20,317 --> 00:39:21,384
你收到我的便条了?
Did you get my note?

747
00:39:21,499 --> 00:39:23,574
是的 是的
Yes, yes,

748
00:39:23,690 --> 00:39:26,122
内容是到这里来以避免一起丑闻
something about coming here to avoid a scandal.

749
00:39:26,231 --> 00:39:28,592
总好过在你府上见面
Better than meeting up at the hall,

750
00:39:28,701 --> 00:39:31,097
人们会议论纷纷的
people might talk.

751
00:39:31,206 --> 00:39:33,601
你干嘛想见我?
Why do you wish to see me?

752
00:39:44,114 --> 00:39:46,854
噢 是的
Oh, yes.

753
00:39:46,967 --> 00:39:52,115
我知道了所有你和McCarthy之间的事情
I know all about you and McCarthy.

754
00:39:52,222 --> 00:39:56,006
我的朋友华生会记下一些事实
My friend Watson will jot down a few facts.

755
00:39:56,119 --> 00:39:57,707
我保证除非很有必要
I promise it will not be used

756
00:39:57,823 --> 00:40:01,927
否则我不会利用它们
unless it is absolutely needed.

757
00:40:02,033 --> 00:40:03,729
请坐下
Do sit down.

758
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:17,199
你不了解那个死鬼McCarthy
You didn't know the dead man McCarthy.

759
00:40:17,307 --> 00:40:20,890
他是魔鬼的化身
He was a devil incarnate.

760
00:40:20,996 --> 00:40:22,620
是上帝保佑 你们才没有落入
God keep you out of the clutches

761
00:40:22,735 --> 00:40:24,289
一个像他这样的人的魔爪之中
of a man such as he.

762
00:40:24,406 --> 00:40:26,908
我被他玩弄于鼓掌已经很多年了
His grip has been upon me these many years

763
00:40:27,014 --> 00:40:30,525
他毁掉了我的生活
and he's blasted my life.

764
00:40:30,634 --> 00:40:36,470
我要先告诉你 我是怎么被他控制的
I'll tell you first how I came to be in his power.

765
00:40:36,583 --> 00:40:40,094
那是60年代 在矿区
It was in the early 60's at the diggings.

766
00:40:40,202 --> 00:40:42,075
那时我还是一个小伙子
I was a young chap then,

767
00:40:42,185 --> 00:40:44,438
热血沸腾 莽莽撞撞
hot blooded and reckless.

768
00:40:44,551 --> 00:40:47,647
呃 我没什么运气
Well, I had no luck with me claim,

769
00:40:47,752 --> 00:40:49,733
于是就上了梁山
took to the bush and came what you'd call

770
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:52,438
成了你们所说的路匪
a highway robber.

771
00:40:52,554 --> 00:40:54,143
我们有一小伙人
There was a little gang of us

772
00:40:54,259 --> 00:40:56,796
过着一种疯狂自由的生活
who lived a wild free life of it.

773
00:40:56,902 --> 00:40:59,476
不时抢劫一个车站
Sticking up a station from time to time

774
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:02,642
或是在路上打劫从矿区来的货车
or stopping the wagon on the road from the diggings.

775
00:41:02,748 --> 00:41:06,675
他们管我叫"巴勒拉特的黑杰克"
They called me Black Jack of Ballarat.

776
00:41:06,784 --> 00:41:09,595
我想那里的人至今还记得
I believe they still remember the Ballarat gang

777
00:41:09,707 --> 00:41:12,697
"巴勒拉特帮"
in the colony.

778
00:41:33,263 --> 00:41:35,171
货车司机就是McCarthy
The wagon driver was McCarthy

779
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:36,739
而我饶了他一命
and I spared him.

780
00:41:36,845 --> 00:41:38,090
滚!
Get out of it!

781
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:39,733
继续 跑啊!
Go on, shift!

782
00:41:39,838 --> 00:41:41,746
别烦着我 快点!
Do a (unintelligible), fast!

783
00:42:04,194 --> 00:42:05,996
我们拿着金子跑了
We got away with the gold.

784
00:42:08,021 --> 00:42:09,894
Mac和我都成了有钱人
And Mac and I were wealthy men

785
00:42:10,004 --> 00:42:13,230
爬到了梦想的巅峰
beyond the dreams of Everest.

786
00:42:13,345 --> 00:42:14,874
我们...
There was...

787
00:42:19,050 --> 00:42:20,958
我们...
There was...

788
00:42:26,532 --> 00:42:28,714
我们成了悬赏通缉的对象
There was a price on our heads.

789
00:42:30,636 --> 00:42:34,182
我决定到英格兰来
I decided to make for England.

790
00:42:34,290 --> 00:42:36,199
我决心安定下来
I determined to settle down

791
00:42:36,309 --> 00:42:40,198
过一种平静而受人尊重的生活
to a quiet and respectable life.

792
00:42:40,310 --> 00:42:41,131
我买下了这处庄园
I bought this estate 

793
00:42:41,131 --> 00:42:44,682
包括这整个村子 甚至这个旅馆
that included the whole village even this inn is mine.

794
00:42:44,797 --> 00:42:47,158
我开始用我的钱做一些好事
I set myself to do a little good with my money

795
00:42:47,269 --> 00:42:51,266
对我所作所为做出弥补
to make up for the way in which I'd earned it.

796
00:42:51,374 --> 00:42:56,000
我结了婚而我的妻子年纪轻轻就去世了
I married and then my darling wife died young.

797
00:42:56,107 --> 00:42:59,166
她给我留下了亲爱的小Alice
She left me my dear little Alice.

798
00:43:01,604 --> 00:43:04,141
你可以说我是个幸福的人
I was a happy man you might say,

799
00:43:04,247 --> 00:43:08,802
直到McCarthy控制了我
until McCarthy laid his grip upon me.

800
00:43:08,910 --> 00:43:10,891
他一路跟踪我
He followed my trail,

801
00:43:10,998 --> 00:43:12,906
他刚到这儿来的时候
when he first came here,

802
00:43:13,016 --> 00:43:16,835
还光着脚丫 衣不遮体
he'd hardly a coat to his back or a boot to his foot.

803
00:43:16,947 --> 00:43:19,235
"我们来了 杰克" 他说
"Here we are, Jack," he said,

804
00:43:19,348 --> 00:43:21,531
"你可以收留我们"
You can have the keeping of us,

805
00:43:21,645 --> 00:43:24,182
"我和我的小男孩"
me and my little boy,

806
00:43:24,289 --> 00:43:26,021
"要是你不愿意..."
and if you don't,

807
00:43:26,133 --> 00:43:29,394
"英格兰可是个法制国家"
England is a fine law-abiding country

808
00:43:29,509 --> 00:43:33,671
"警察总是随便就能找到一个"
and there's always a policeman handy.

809
00:43:33,787 --> 00:43:36,219
我就只好束手待毙 被他敲诈
I was a sitting duck for blackmail.

810
00:43:36,328 --> 00:43:38,095
根本摆脱不了他
There was no shaking him off,

811
00:43:38,205 --> 00:43:39,272
没完没了
there was no rest,

812
00:43:39,389 --> 00:43:39,990
不得安宁
no peace,

813
00:43:39,990 --> 00:43:40,991
不能忘却
no forgetfulness.

814
00:43:40,992 --> 00:43:41,994
无论我去到哪里
Turn there I would,

815
00:43:41,995 --> 00:43:45,072
都能看到他那张狡猾狞笑的脸
there was his cunning, grinning face at me elbow.

816
00:43:45,073 --> 00:43:46,998
他一定要得到他想得到的东西
Whatever he wanted he must have

817
00:43:46,998 --> 00:43:48,048
而不管他要什么
and whatever it was

818
00:43:48,049 --> 00:43:50,017
我都得无条件地给他
I gave him without question.

819
00:43:50,018 --> 00:43:55,359
土地 金钱 房子
Land, money, houses

820
00:43:55,359 --> 00:43:58,970
直到最后他又提出了一个我不能满足的要求
until at last he asked the thing I could not give.

821
00:43:59,569 --> 00:44:03,672
他想要Alice
He asked for Alice.

822
00:44:03,779 --> 00:44:06,804
他的儿子和我的女儿一起长大
His son and my girl had grown up.

823
00:44:06,911 --> 00:44:08,785
他知道我身体不佳
He knew I was in weak health.

824
00:44:08,894 --> 00:44:11,290
对他来说要是他儿子能接管所有财产
It seemed a fine stroke to him that his son

825
00:44:11,399 --> 00:44:14,459
那可是再好不过
should step into the whole property.

826
00:44:14,564 --> 00:44:17,375
我坚决反对
There I was firm.

827
00:44:17,487 --> 00:44:19,539
我不会让他那该死的血统
I would not have his cursed stock

828
00:44:19,646 --> 00:44:20,749
来玷污我们家的血脉
mixed with mine.

829
00:44:20,863 --> 00:44:23,365
倒不是我不喜欢那孩子
Not that I had any dislike for the lad,

830
00:44:23,472 --> 00:44:25,311
可是他身上流着他父亲的血
but his father's blood was in him

831
00:44:25,421 --> 00:44:27,923
这就够了
and that was enough.

832
00:44:28,030 --> 00:44:29,584
我立场坚定
I stood firm.

833
00:44:29,701 --> 00:44:31,397
McCarthy威胁我
McCarthy threatened,

834
00:44:31,510 --> 00:44:34,140
我说他用最毒辣的手段也吓不倒我
I braved him to do his worst.

835
00:44:35,164 --> 00:44:36,752
我们约好在两家之间的湖边见面
We arranged to meet at the Mirror,

836
00:44:36,868 --> 00:44:40,451
把事情说清楚
halfway between our two houses to talk it over.

837
00:44:40,556 --> 00:44:42,500
按我说的去做
- Do as you're told.

838
00:44:42,609 --> 00:44:43,782
James
James.

839
00:44:43,897 --> 00:44:45,316
我听着他的话
As I listened to his talk all that was

840
00:44:45,317 --> 00:44:48,292
心里所有的愤恨越来越强烈
black and bitter seemed to come upper most

841
00:44:48,293 --> 00:44:50,495
他催促他儿子娶我的女儿
and he was urging his son to marry my daughter

842
00:44:50,495 --> 00:44:52,894
丝毫没有顾及她的感受
with as little regard for what she might think

843
00:44:52,895 --> 00:44:54,712
活活把她当成了街上卖身的妓女
as a slut from off the streets.

844
00:44:54,713 --> 00:44:57,582
-我们以前就谈过这个 -按我说的去做 小子!
-We have been through all this before. -Do as I tell you, boy,

845
00:44:57,582 --> 00:44:59,575
你这该死的不听话的小杂种!
you damn disobedient little bastard.

846
00:44:59,575 --> 00:45:01,166
一想到我和我心爱的一切
It drove me mad to think that I

847
00:45:01,167 --> 00:45:02,666
将落入这个人的魔爪
and all that I held dear

848
00:45:02,666 --> 00:45:04,784
我都快疯了
should be in the power of such a man.

849
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:07,933
-这是我的生活! -我要按我的方式去过!
It's my life and I'm going to run it the way I like.

850
00:45:07,933 --> 00:45:10,637
我快死了 也没什么指望了
I was a dying and desperate man.

851
00:45:10,637 --> 00:45:12,934
如果我能让这张邪恶的嘴巴永远闭上
If I could silence that foul tongue I could still

852
00:45:12,935 --> 00:45:16,077
那我还能挽救我 和我的家庭在这个溪谷里的名声
save me and my family's reputation in this valley.

853
00:45:16,185 --> 00:45:18,166
给我滚开
Get off out of it.

854
00:45:58,841 --> 00:46:01,129
是我干的  福尔摩斯先生
I did it, Mr. Holmes,

855
00:46:01,242 --> 00:46:04,018
再来一次 我还会这么干
and I would do it again.

856
00:46:04,130 --> 00:46:05,659
虽然我罪孽深重
Deeply though I've sinned

857
00:46:05,765 --> 00:46:09,999
但我也过了一辈子痛苦的日子做出了补偿
I've lived a life of martyrdom to atone for it.

858
00:46:10,115 --> 00:46:11,926
如果让我的女儿
If my girl should become entangled

859
00:46:11,926 --> 00:46:13,691
也经受我曾受过的痛苦
in the same meshes which held me

860
00:46:13,803 --> 00:46:16,756
那我是绝对不答应的
was more than I could suffer.

861
00:46:16,865 --> 00:46:19,189
我把他打倒了 心里一点也不后悔
I struck him down with no more compunction

862
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:23,926
他就是一只凶猛恶毒的野兽
than if he'd been some foul and venomous beast.

863
00:46:28,590 --> 00:46:30,931
这就是事情的经过 先生们
That is the true story gentlemen

864
00:46:34,470 --> 00:46:36,973
千真万确
of all that occurred.

865
00:46:43,308 --> 00:46:45,288
对你的判决不是由我来做
It is not for me to judge you,

866
00:46:45,395 --> 00:46:49,374
但是我希望 我们永远也不用经受这样的诱惑
but I hope that we may never expose to such temptation.

867
00:46:50,581 --> 00:46:52,793
我也希望不用 先生
I pray not, sir.

868
00:46:53,990 --> 00:46:55,717
我是个快要死的人了
I'm a dying man.

869
00:46:58,165 --> 00:47:01,185
我患糖尿病很多年了
I've had the diabetes for years.

870
00:47:01,680 --> 00:47:06,298
我的医生说 我是否能活上一个月都成问题
My doctor says it's a question  of whether I shall live a month

871
00:47:06,411 --> 00:47:08,508
而我想要死在自己家里
and I'd rather die under me own roof

872
00:47:08,508 --> 00:47:09,969
而不是在监狱中
than in a jail.

873
00:47:09,970 --> 00:47:11,838
不会的 不过McCarthy必须获释
No, McCarthy must be got off, however.

874
00:47:12,605 --> 00:47:13,434
老天助我
God help me but

875
00:47:13,434 --> 00:47:17,357
不过我也不想那男孩受到伤害
I wouldn't let that young man come to harm.

876
00:47:17,358 --> 00:47:19,328
我向你保证
I'll give you my word that I'd have spoken out

877
00:47:19,328 --> 00:47:21,788
如果审判对他不利 我会说出真相的
if it went against him at the assizes.

878
00:47:21,895 --> 00:47:23,864
很高兴听到你这样说
I'm very glad to hear you say so.

879
00:47:23,864 --> 00:47:25,306
要不是为了我亲爱的女儿
I'd have spoken now

880
00:47:25,548 --> 00:47:28,949
我现在就会把真相公诸于众
if it had not been for my dear girl.

881
00:47:28,950 --> 00:47:32,010
这样会让她心碎的
It would break her heart.

882
00:47:35,290 --> 00:47:38,346
她要是听到我被捕了 她会心碎的
It'll break her heart when she hears that I'm arrested.

883
00:47:38,347 --> 00:47:40,573
不会到那个地步
It may not come to that.

884
00:47:43,017 --> 00:47:45,593
我们不是警察
We're not the police.

885
00:47:46,527 --> 00:47:49,653
我也不是政府的什么密探
I am no official agent.

886
00:47:50,834 --> 00:47:53,396
我是应你女儿的要求来的
I'm here at your daughter's request.

887
00:47:55,833 --> 00:47:57,956
-Alice? -是Alice
-Alice? -Alice.

888
00:48:00,750 --> 00:48:04,410
那你打算怎么做?
Then what do you intend to do?

889
00:48:04,517 --> 00:48:07,612
考虑到你的健康 我什么也不打算做
In view of your health, nothing.

890
00:48:07,718 --> 00:48:10,256
你自己都意识到 你将去到更高的一级法庭(天庭)
You are yourself aware that you'll have to answer

891
00:48:10,360 --> 00:48:14,915
来为你所做的事情承担后果
for your deed at a higher court than the assizes.

892
00:48:15,025 --> 00:48:16,684
如果小McCarthy被宣告有罪
If young McCarthy's condemned

893
00:48:16,798 --> 00:48:18,909
我将不得不公开你的供词
I shall be forced to use this confession.

894
00:48:19,025 --> 00:48:23,349
要是他被判无罪 那这份供词就永远不会被人看到
If not, it will never be seen by mortal eye

895
00:48:23,350 --> 00:48:27,469
而不管你是否在世 你的秘密都将是安全的
and your secret whether you be alive or dead, shall be safe.

896
00:48:49,799 --> 00:48:51,552
那么再见吧
Farewell then.

897
00:48:56,464 --> 00:49:00,038
在你自己要离开人世的时候
Your own deathbeds when they come

898
00:49:00,151 --> 00:49:03,938
当你一想到你曾给我带来的安宁
a little bit easier for a  thought of the peace

899
00:49:03,939 --> 00:49:07,410
你会死得更心安的
 that you've given to mine.

900
00:49:29,030 --> 00:49:32,149
噢 上帝啊 帮帮我们吧
Oh God, help us.

901
00:49:41,625 --> 00:49:45,515
Turner John Stewart 于8月16日
Turner, John Stewart, 16th of August,

902
00:49:45,626 --> 00:49:47,737
在Cheshire郡的Boscombe宅邸Cheshire
Boscombe Hall Cheshire.

903
00:49:47,854 --> 00:49:49,169
在长期与病魔斗争后
After a long illness,

904
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:53,349
与世长辞 Alice敬爱的父亲
bravely born, beloved father of Alice.

905
00:49:53,454 --> 00:49:58,390
我们可以在小McCarthy的审讯中
Well, we're free to use that confession

906
00:49:58,500 --> 00:50:00,223
随意地使用那份供词了
at young McCarthy's trial.

907
00:50:00,224 --> 00:50:02,424
不 绝对不要
No, by no means.

908
00:50:02,425 --> 00:50:05,058
我的承诺是除非McCarthy被判有罪
My promise was it would not be used

909
00:50:05,058 --> 00:50:06,441
否则我们将不会使用它
unless McCarthy is condemned

910
00:50:06,441 --> 00:50:08,467
而我想我已经给出了足够的反驳理由
and I think I've given enough objections

911
00:50:08,468 --> 00:50:10,760
足以确保他无罪释放
to the charge to insure his acquittal.

912
00:50:10,761 --> 00:50:12,755
希望如此
Well, I hope so.

913
00:51:29,301 --> 00:51:31,353
我爱你
I love you.

914
00:51:31,469 --> 00:51:34,101
我也爱你
I love you too.

915
00:51:34,217 --> 00:51:36,511
嫁给我好吗?
Will you marry me?

916
